<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">What is a pound?</h2>



<p>A pound is a unit of weight commonly used in the United States and some =
other countries. It=E2=80=99s abbreviated as =E2=80=9Clb=E2=80=9D and is pa=
rt of the <a href=3D"https://myplantbasedbowl.com/metric-system-vs-imperial=
-system/">imperial system of measurement</a>. In everyday life, we use poun=
ds to measure body weight, food ingredients, and various household items.</=
p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How many grams are in a pound?</h2>



<p>Understanding the conversion between pounds and grams is fairly easy:</p=
>



<p><strong>1 pound equals 453.592 grams</strong></p>



<p>For everyday use, many people round this number to 454 grams.&nbsp;</p>



