<p><strong>To convert grams to pounds, use this simple formula:</strong></p=
>



<p>Pounds =3D Grams =C3=B7 453.592</p>



<p>If a recipe calls for 500 grams of flour, the conversion to pounds would=
 look like this:</p>



<p>Pounds =3D 500 grams =C3=B7 453.592 =E2=89=88 1.102 pounds</p>



<p>So, 500 grams of flour is approximately 1.1 pounds.</p>



<p><strong>To convert pounds to grams, use this formula:</strong></p>



<p>Grams =3D Pounds =C3=97 453.592</p>



<p>So if a recipe calls for 1.5 pounds of flour, the conversion to grams wo=
uld be:</p>



<p>Grams =3D 1.5 pounds x 453.592 =E2=89=88 680.388 grams</p>



<p>So, 1.5 pounds of flour is approximately 680 grams.</p>



